Subject: Hub agency/my comments
Body:
David,

Please change the date on the draft so that we won't confuse it with the 
prior drafts.

I would delete "specifically" from 2.10 (c), and add "or later ratify such 
transaction" (or something to that effect), just in case they later learn and 
accept the transaction.  

In 2.10 (x), add to "due to an inability to pay, or other credit reason".  In 
(y), add "or a contractual defense to payment" [could be force majeure, etc]

Again in 2.10, third sentence from the end "any interest, penalties, 
attorneys fees and court costspayable by the Hub Shipper...;

3.3  Delete "prior" before "approval", and add "or ratification" in the 
redlined section on refunds.


Thanks,

Kay
summary:
- Kay requests David to change the draft's date to avoid confusion with prior drafts.
- Kay suggests changes to section 2.10: delete "specifically" from (c), add "or later ratify such transaction", add to (x) "due to an inability to pay, or other credit reason", add to (y) "or a contractual defense to payment".
- Kay requests a change to the third sentence from the end of section 2.10: "any interest, penalties, attorneys fees and court costs payable by the Hub Shipper".
- Kay requests changes to section 3.3: Delete "prior" before "approval" and add "or ratification" in the redlined section on refunds.
action_item: Change the date on the draft to avoid confusion with prior drafts.
draft_reply:
Dear Kay,

Thanks for the feedback. I have made the requested changes to the draft.

Specifically, I have:

*   Adjusted the date.
*   Removed "specifically" from 2.10 (c) and added "or later ratify such transaction".
*   Added to 2.10 (x), "due to an inability to pay, or other credit reason".
*   Added to 2.10 (y), "or a contractual defense to payment".
*   Corrected the wording in the third sentence from the end of 2.10, "any interest, penalties, attorneys fees and court costs payable by the Hub Shipper...".
*   Deleted "prior" before "approval" and added "or ratification" in the redlined section on refunds in 3.3.

Please let me know if you have any other changes.

Best regards,

David
demo@gmail.com

Kate,

Please take some time over the weekend to consider what might be helpful for the desk (ie. collecting pertinent weather information, transmission derates, day-ahead prices, congestion, historical spreads, etc.) and let me know on Monday or Tuesday what we can do.  Take your time but have a good weekend.

Bill

Subject: Per Zachary Streight
Body:
All,

There has been some concern about the lack of clarity regarding what 
functionality is ready for user acceptance testing in the staging 
environment.  To attempt to solve this problem, we have come up with a simple 
process that will enhance communication and will allow everyone on the team 
to know what functionality is in staging waiting for user acceptance signoff 
prior to a release to production.  Please read the attached one page document 
that details the proposed process.  Let me know if you have any questions.

Thanks,
Zach
summary:
- Zach addressed concerns about clarity on functionality ready for User Acceptance Testing (UAT) in the staging environment.
- A new process, detailed in an attached document, aims to improve communication and transparency regarding functionality awaiting UAT sign-off.
- Zach requests team members to review the document and ask any questions.
action_item: Read the attached one-page document detailing the proposed process.
draft_reply:
Dear Zach,

Thank you for sharing the proposed process document. I've reviewed it and appreciate the initiative to clarify the staging environment's status for user acceptance testing. The document seems well-structured and addresses the concerns effectively. I don't have any immediate questions, but I will be sure to reach out if any arise as I begin to utilize the new process.

Thanks again,

Demo

Subject: GPM Dumas

Gary
